  "accepted_findings": [
    "Near topology now uses eight golden-angle branchlets per parent shoot, three tertiary branches per branchlet, and twenty-two attached leaves per branchlet rather than six, two, and fourteen.",
    "Shortening branchlets from 30-49 cm to 24-40 cm while increasing density produces materially fuller foreground foliage without enlarging leaf cards or changing the 2-3.5 cm visible-leaf contract.",
    "Open-grown near foliage rises from 19,656 to 41,184 attached cards and its branchlet mesh rises from 243,834 to 468,872 render vertices; every form derives actual anchor counts from generated topology.",
    "A bounded 0.38-intensity opposing fill plus a reduced 0.75 front fill reveals bark texture in both turntable azimuths under fixed exposure without changing bark material response or adding emissive fill.",
    "All eight forms retain distinct v8 life-history silhouettes and stable 60 m and 150 m far-crown representations after the denser near-detail change.",
    "The final UE 5.8 Metal run completes forty captures with zero map-check errors/warnings, no material compile errors, and no texture no-miplevel warnings."
  ],
  "rejection_reasons": [
    "The denser closeups still expose branchlet and tertiary intersections, especially around parent-shoot junctions; density improved, but foreground ramification is not yet photoreal.",
    "The shared primary-branch cadence remains visible in whole-tree views and still needs per-form branch-origin and ramification grammar variation.",
    "The denser non-Nanite near meshes roughly double foreground geometry cost and have no measured desktop or VR frame-time, memory, or draw-distance evidence.",
    "SimpleGrassWind parameters exist but temporal branch-versus-leaf phase coherence, amplitude bounds, and motion-vector behavior remain uncaptured.",
    "Mixed native species, sapling, understory, deadwood, and source-matched corridor ecology remain absent."
  ],
